  "response": "No, a single Jio SIM cannot be simultaneously used on two different mobile handsets. Each SIM card can only be active in one device at a time. If you insert the same SIM into another phone, it will deactivate in the previous device and become active in the new device. To use the same number on multiple devices, you would need to:\n\n1. Physically move the SIM card between devices\n2. Get a dual SIM or multi-SIM connection from Jio\n3. Use Jio's eSIM facility on compatible devices",
